race.comment: ENCHANTED JENNI (4) is flying having won three in a row, far too good over this route two back, kicking back to beat a handy one at Caulfield Heath after looking beaten in the straight. This doesn't look any harder and she can notch up another victory. SHINY NEW DEEL (2) was well backed last time but led far too quickly at Bendigo, dropping right out late. Fresh for this now, if he gets it right early he'll take plenty of catching. VIVACISSIMO (7) has been right there in two runs back from a spell, beaten just half a length at Geelong last time out. Still on the up and with luck from the inside gate she can prove very hard to hold out. FAREWELL TO EIRE (8) can mix her form a bit but the last run at Caulfield Heath was rock solid. She draws for a soft run here and her best form gives her a good chance. MASTERFUL (3) was suited by the strong pace two back, struggling in a tougher race at Caulfield last time. He can bounce back.
